  "text": "Maternal transmission of gonococcal infection remains a problem in developing countries. [CITATION_1] This results in morbidity in both the mother and the baby. In this Ethiopian study, there was a high level of antimicrobial resistance in the gonococcal isolates. A solution to this may emerge from a study performed in New Zealand, which suggests that an outer membrane vesicle meningococcal vaccine known as MENZ-B may have a 31% effectiveness against gonorrhea (95% CI 21-39%).",
